-- Abbas Names Street After Putin in His Bethlehem Neighborhood
-- B y   S t e p a n   K r a v c h e n k o
-- 2012-06-26T07:03:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-26/abbas-names-street-after-putin-in-his-bethlehem-neighborhood.html
Palestinian Authority President
 Mahmoud Abbas  named a street after Russian President Vladimir Putin near his residence in the West Bank town of Bethlehem.  The street is officially being renamed today, during
Putin’s visit, according to a plaque on a wall of an
administrative building in Bethlehem. Abbas named a street after
Putin’s predecessor, now-Prime Minister Dmitry Medvedev, in
Jericho near the Dead Sea in January.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Stepan Kravchenko in Moscow at 
 skravchenko@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
